Gnathosoma. Stylophore notched anteriorly, 75 ( 78 – 70 ) long, 54 ( 55 – 53 ) wide; eupathidium su about 2.5 times longer than broad, 3.9 ( 3.5–4.5 ) long, 1.7 ( 1.5–1.8 ) wide, narrowed distally, slightly longer than palptarsal solenidion ω 3.5 ( 3–4 ). Eupathidium ul’’ 7.4 ( 7–8 ) longer than ul’ , 5.6 ( 5–6.5 ) (
Fig. 20
). Peritreme as in female (
Fig. 21
).

Legs. Empodia clawlike with 3 pairs of proximoventral hairs increasing in length with the rank of the leg between leg I and leg III (
Figs. 17–19
). Leg setal counts as follows:

Solenidion of distal member of duplex of tarsus I ( ω ’’) 59 ( 55–64 ) about twice as long as solenidion of proximal duplex ( ω ’) 33 ( 30–37 ) (
Fig. 15
). Fastigial seta ft ’’short 8.5 ( 7–10 ), half length of ft ’ 17 ( 15–19 ). Tarsus I with 3 tactile setae and 3 solenidia proximal to proximal duplex setae, dorsolateral distal solenidion ( ω’’ 1 ) 25.5 ( 24–27 ) longer than distance between its base and that of proximal duplex. On leg II, solenidion of duplex ( ω’’ ) 23 ( 21–25 ) twice as long as ft ’’ 11.5 ( 11–13 ) (
Fig. 16
).

Aedeagus. Aedeagus without distinct knob, bent dorsad near at right angle to dorsal margin of shaft, weakly sigmoid, with tapering distal part and acute tip pointing caudad (
Fig. 22
).
